However, the smaller molecular size relative to proline, attributed to the oxidized side chain, reduces van der Waals interactions, which is expected to reduce the melting point, here estimated to be a decrease of -80 degrees. Thus, considering the effects of the functional groups, the melting point of 5-oxo-l-proline would be predicted to be lower than that of proline itself.
